        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "To produce a value of n for which sn = 2015 (mod 10000), we take n = 3m + 1 for some nonnega- tive integer m for which s3m+1 = 30m + 15. We must also have 30m = 2000 (mod 10000), or equivalently m = 400 (mod 1000). By taking m = 1400, we ensure that m = 2 (mod 3), so sm = 10m + 7; this ensures that Sn does indeed equal 30m + 15 = 42015, as desired.",
        "bbox": [
          0.12705882352941175,
          0.11090909090909092,
          0.49098039215686273,
          0.21272727272727274
        ],
        "order": 2
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "eu_id": "EU-0003",
    "kind": "text_cluster_panel",
