        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "Consequently, if we write n in base 3, then f (n) = 0 unless the expansion ends with 2 followed by a string of 1s of length k ≥ 0, in which case f (n) = (−1)k+1.",
        "bbox": [
          0.12705882352941175,
